    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="2" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Motley</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 79.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vienna,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 31, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to state that, upon the
                            26th of October, his Imperial Royal Majesty accepted the resignation by
                            his excellency Count Rechberg of his functions as minister of foreign
                            affairs and of the imperial household. The fact was communicated on the
                            same day by circulars to the various foreign legations at Vienna. On the
                            following day a circular from Count Mensdorff Ponilly announced his
                            appointment to the functions resigned by Count Rechberg.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to remain, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. LOTHROP MOTLEY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
